==Description==

The '''Std ViewCreate''' command creates a new [[3D_View|3D View]] for the active document. Additional 3D Views can be useful if you want to inspect the model from multiple directions or at different zoom levels.

[[Image:ViewCreate1.png|400px]]
{{Caption|The FreeCAD interface with multiple 3D Views}}

==Usage==

# Select the {{MenuCommand|View → [[Image:Std_ViewCreate.svg|16px]] New 3D View}} option from the menu.

==Options==

* Select the {{MenuCommand|Windows → Cascade}} or {{MenuCommand|Windows → Tile}} option from the menu to rearrange the 3D Views.


